title: The Fall
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/31PW4XZ

by i_need_a_creative_outlet

Crowley never meant to fall, of course. When asked, he liked to say that he sauntered vaguely downwards, but that was just to preserve his dignity. “Sauntering vaguely downwards” implied some sort of choice– a decision consciously made and executed with a certain amount of style and attitude. “Spending time with the wrong people” supported the swaggering bad-boy image he was expected to uphold, and the idea of rebellion against unjust authority was a rather romantic concept.
In reality, he had not been given a choice, but saying you had been unceremoniously dumped into an infinite pit of boiling sulphur didn’t exactly sound as jazzy.

summary: That viral video from a few years ago where that husband that just came out of surgery and didn’t remember his wife but with...
body:
That viral video from a few years ago where that husband that just came out of surgery and didn’t remember his wife but with Crowley and Aziraphale.

Like I don’t know how it happens, maybe Crowley gets hit by a car or something but somehow he ends up in the hospital heavily anesthetized and then Aziraphale shows up.

“Did the doctor send you?”

“Certainly not,” Azirphale sniffed, not knowing what was going on.

“You may be the prettiest person I have ever seen”

“Well- that’s very kind-“

“Are you a model? Are you an angel”

“Of course I am-“

“Of course you are.”

“Are you alright, my dear?”

“Who are you? What’s your name?”

“I’m Aziraphale. Your- well- your angel-“

“You’re my angel? Holy shit. How long?”

“Since the beginning.”

“Do we have children.”

“No. We do have something of a godson, lovely young boy, but nothing official, I suppose.”

“Oh man, have we kissed yet”

“Crowley-” Aziraphale flushed, looking away.

“Oh my god, i hit the jackpot- Let me see your face, woah your teeth are perfect, turn around- for me-“

“Crowley, please,”

summary: Ok, I haven't read Good Omens yet but I saw around here that Crowley kind of slept around? Even if it wasn't addressed on the...
body: Ok, I haven’t read Good Omens yet but I saw around here that Crowley kind of slept around? Even if it wasn’t addressed on the show. So what if Aziraphale got curious about humans kissing and their relationships and all that stuff, but he doesn’t say anything until after the end-of-the-world-that-never-happens, and Crowley knows what it’s like, but he also kind of wants to tempt the angel into doing something so human. And after they kiss for the first time, Crowley understands the whole difference between kissing someone and Kissing Someone humans always talk about

body: Just finished Good Omens and all I want to say is Crowley reminded me SO much of Brian Kinney from Queer As Folk. That whole ‘I’m a bad guy who doesn’t need anyone’ facade while they’re literally the softest bean underneath is exactly the same and I love them BOTH.

body:
In the human tongue we say “I love you.” To convey affection. But sometimes when we’ve known someone long enough we say:

“You’re just enough of a bastard to be worth knowing.” And I think that’s beautiful.

summary: Watching Good Omens is interesting because Heaven and Hell have both gotten so obsessed with being Lawful, they’ve forgotten to...
body: Watching Good Omens is interesting because Heaven and Hell have both gotten so obsessed with being Lawful, they’ve forgotten to be good and evil. All they care about is if they’re following orders or not. And it is so clear in the last episode, especially Crowley’s comments at the end, both with his impersonation of Aziraphale and that prediction.
